---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Aviation Desk" description="Learn how Aviation Desk collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you use our website.">
  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-wrap">

      <header class="legal-header">
        <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-updated">Last Updated: July 15, 2026</p>
      </header>

      <nav class="legal-toc" aria-label="Table of Contents">
        <p class="toc-title">Contents</p>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#introduction">Introduction</a></li>
          <li><a href="#information-we-collect">Information We Collect</a></li>
          <li><a href="#how-we-use-your-information">How We Use Your Information</a></li>
          <li><a href="#cookies">Cookies and Tracking Technologies</a></li>
          <li><a href="#third-party">Third-Party Services and Links</a></li>
          <li><a href="#advertising">Advertising</a></li>
          <li><a href="#data-sharing">Data Sharing and Disclosure</a></li>
          <li><a href="#data-retention">Data Retention</a></li>
          <li><a href="#data-security">Data Security</a></li>
          <li><a href="#your-rights">Your Privacy Rights</a></li>
          <li><a href="#children">Children's Privacy</a></li>
          <li><a href="#international">International Data Transfers</a></li>
          <li><a href="#changes">Changes to This Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="#contact">Contact Us</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <article class="legal-body">

        <!-- 1. Introduction -->
        <section id="introduction">
          <h2><span class="section-num">1.</span> Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            Welcome to Aviation Desk (&ldquo;Aviation Desk,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website at
            <a href="https://aviationdesk.vercel.app/" class="inline-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://aviationdesk.vercel.app/</a>
            (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;), including any content, features, and services offered on it.
          </p>
          <p>
            By accessing or using the Site, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the terms of this policy, please do not access the Site.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 2. Information We Collect -->
        <section id="information-we-collect">
          <h2><span class="section-num">2.</span> Information We Collect</h2>

          <h3>a. Information You Provide Directly</h3>
          <p>We may collect information that you voluntarily provide to us, such as:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Your name and email address, if you subscribe to a newsletter, contact us, or leave a comment.</li>
            <li>Any information you include in messages sent to us via a contact form or email.</li>
            <li>Information you provide if you follow or interact with our social media accounts, including our X (Twitter) account <a href="https://x.com/aman0arc" class="inline-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@aman0arc</a>.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>b. Information Collected Automatically</h3>
          <p>When you visit the Site, we may automatically collect certain information about your device and usage, including:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>IP address and approximate geographic location</li>
            <li>Browser type and version</li>
            <li>Device type and operating system</li>
            <li>Pages visited, time spent on pages, and referring/exit pages</li>
            <li>Date and time of your visit</li>
            <li>Clickstream data and general browsing behavior on the Site</li>
          </ul>
          <p>This information is typically collected through cookies, log files, and similar tracking technologies (see <a href="#cookies" class="inline-link">Section 4</a>).</p>
        </section>

        <!-- 3. How We Use Your Information -->
        <section id="how-we-use-your-information">
          <h2><span class="section-num">3.</span> How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p>We use the information we collect for purposes including:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Operating, maintaining, and improving the Site and its content</li>
            <li>Understanding how visitors use the Site, to improve article quality, layout, and navigation</li>
            <li>Responding to inquiries, comments, or requests you submit</li>
            <li>Sending newsletters or updates, if you have opted in</li>
            <li>Monitoring and analyzing usage trends and preferences</li>
            <li>Detecting, preventing, and addressing technical issues, fraud, or abuse</li>
            <li>Complying with applicable legal obligations</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies -->
        <section id="cookies">
          <h2><span class="section-num">4.</span> Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
          <p>
            The Site may use cookies, web beacons, and similar tracking technologies to enhance your browsing experience and analyze traffic. Cookies are small data files stored on your device.
          </p>
          <p>We may use the following types of cookies:</p>
          <div class="cookie-table-wrap">
            <table class="cookie-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Cookie Type</th>
                  <th>Purpose</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Essential</strong></td>
                  <td>Necessary for the Site to function properly</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Analytics</strong></td>
                  <td>Help us understand how visitors interact with the Site (e.g., via Google Analytics)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Preference</strong></td>
                  <td>Remember your settings and preferences</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Advertising</strong></td>
                  <td>If the Site displays third-party advertisements, these may be used to deliver relevant ads</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <p>
            You can control or disable cookies through your browser settings. Please note that disabling cookies may affect the functionality of the Site.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 5. Third-Party Services and Links -->
        <section id="third-party">
          <h2><span class="section-num">5.</span> Third-Party Services and Links</h2>

          <h3>a. Third-Party Service Providers</h3>
          <p>We may use third-party services to help operate and improve the Site, including but not limited to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Vercel</strong> &mdash; for website hosting and deployment</li>
            <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> (or similar analytics tools) &mdash; for traffic and usage analysis</li>
            <li><strong>Social media platforms</strong> (such as X/Twitter) for content sharing and embedded posts</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            These third parties may collect information sent by your browser as part of a web page request, such as cookies or your IP address, in accordance with their own privacy policies.
          </p>

          <h3>b. Third-Party Links</h3>
          <p>
            The Site may contain links to third-party websites, news sources, or services not operated by us. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these external sites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 6. Advertising -->
        <section id="advertising">
          <h2><span class="section-num">6.</span> Advertising</h2>
          <p>
            If Aviation Desk displays advertisements (including through networks such as Google AdSense), those third-party vendors may use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this Site or other websites.
          </p>
          <p>
            You may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting
            <a href="https://adssettings.google.com/" class="inline-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google&rsquo;s Ads Settings</a>
            or the
            <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" class="inline-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Digital Advertising Alliance&rsquo;s opt-out page</a>,
            where applicable.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 7. Data Sharing and Disclosure -->
        <section id="data-sharing">
          <h2><span class="section-num">7.</span> Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
          <p><strong>We do not sell your personal information.</strong> We may share information in the following circumstances:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>With service providers who perform functions on our behalf (e.g., hosting, analytics)</li>
            <li>To comply with legal obligations, court orders, or governmental requests</li>
            <li>To protect and defend our rights, property, or the safety of our users</li>
            <li>In connection with a business transfer, such as a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- 8. Data Retention -->
        <section id="data-retention">
          <h2><span class="section-num">8.</span> Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 9. Data Security -->
        <section id="data-security">
          <h2><span class="section-num">9.</span> Data Security</h2>
          <p>
            We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures designed to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 10. Your Privacy Rights -->
        <section id="your-rights">
          <h2><span class="section-num">10.</span> Your Privacy Rights</h2>
          <p>Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information:</p>

          <div class="rights-block">
            <h4>For Users in India</h4>
            <p>
              Under the Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023, you have the right to access, correct, and request erasure of your personal data, and to withdraw consent where processing is based on consent.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rights-block">
            <h4>For Users in the European Economic Area (GDPR)</h4>
            <p>
              You have the right to access, rectify, erase, restrict, or object to the processing of your personal data, and the right to data portability, subject to applicable legal exceptions.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rights-block">
            <h4>For California Residents (CCPA/CPRA)</h4>
            <p>
              You have the right to know what personal information is collected, to request deletion, and to opt out of the sale or sharing of personal information. <em>Note: Aviation Desk does not sell personal information.</em>
            </p>
          </div>

          <p>
            To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details in <a href="#contact" class="inline-link">Section 14</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 11. Children's Privacy -->
        <section id="children">
          <h2><span class="section-num">11.</span> Children&rsquo;s Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            The Site is not directed to children under the age of 13 (or the applicable age of consent in your jurisdiction), and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected such information, we will take steps to delete it promptly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 12. International Data Transfers -->
        <section id="international">
          <h2><span class="section-num">12.</span> International Data Transfers</h2>
          <p>
            As the Site is hosted using services that may operate servers in various countries, your information may be transferred to, stored, and processed in a country other than your own. By using the Site, you consent to such transfers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 13. Changes to This Privacy Policy -->
        <section id="changes">
          <h2><span class="section-num">13.</span> Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for legal, operational, or regulatory reasons. The updated version will be indicated by a revised &ldquo;Last Updated&rdquo; date, and we encourage you to review this policy periodically.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 14. Contact Us -->
        <section id="contact">
          <h2><span class="section-num">14.</span> Contact Us</h2>
          <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, you may contact us at:</p>
          <div class="contact-block">
            <p><strong>Aviation Desk</strong></p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:contact@aviationdesk.com" class="inline-link">contact@aviationdesk.com</a></p>
            <p>X (Twitter): <a href="https://x.com/aman0arc" class="inline-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@aman0arc</a></p>
          </div>
        </section>

      </article>

      <div class="legal-back">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; Back to Home</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
